# tkv2 - hstack wrap: optional flex-wrap for the horizontal-row layout primitive (std-ui-hstack-wrap)

Slice `std-ui-hstack-wrap` (`specs/std-ui-hstack-wrap.md`): `hstack` accepts a new
`wrap: Boolean = false` parameter (in its first, non-curried parameter group, before the
curried `(children: TkNode*)` group) that `lower.ssc` resolves to an extra `flex-wrap:wrap`
CSS fragment. `View` is opaque to `.ssc` (see `specs/std-ui-select.md` "Why no new extern
def"), so — mirroring `tests/conformance/tkv2-button-variant.ssc`'s own TkNode-field-
assertion style — this conformance test asserts the `wrap` field threads from `hstack(...)`
to `HStackNode` unchanged (including the no-argument default and an explicit `false`), and
that `lower()` does not throw for either value, on both lanes. The actual rendered CSS
`flex-wrap:wrap` fragment (that it appears only when `wrap = true`, and that the `wrap =
false` style string is byte-identical to pre-slice output) was verified at the Scala level;
see `HStackWrapTest.scala` and `specs/std-ui-hstack-wrap.md` § Results.

[hstack](std/ui/layout.ssc)
[HStackNode, TkNode](std/ui/nodes.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)
[text](std/ui/typography.ssc)

```scalascript
val a = text("a")
val b = text("b")

// No `wrap` argument at all — stays the pre-existing default (false), backward
// compatible with every call site that predates this slice.
val defaultRow = hstack(gap = 8)(a, b)
defaultRow match
  case HStackNode(gap, kids, wrap) => println(gap.toString + ":" + kids.length.toString + ":" + wrap.toString)
  case _                           => println("?")
val defaultView = lower(defaultRow, defaultTheme)
println("default-built")

// wrap = true threads through unchanged and lowers without throwing.
val wrapRow = hstack(gap = 8, wrap = true)(a, b)
wrapRow match
  case HStackNode(gap, kids, wrap) => println(gap.toString + ":" + kids.length.toString + ":" + wrap.toString)
  case _                           => println("?")
val wrapView = lower(wrapRow, defaultTheme)
println("wrap-built")

// wrap = false explicitly threads through identically to the default (no
// separate "explicit false" code path).
val noWrapRow = hstack(gap = 8, wrap = false)(a, b)
noWrapRow match
  case HStackNode(gap, kids, wrap) => println(gap.toString + ":" + kids.length.toString + ":" + wrap.toString)
  case _                           => println("?")
val noWrapView = lower(noWrapRow, defaultTheme)
println("hstack-wrap-built")
```
